content:
ICompositionElement Interface

Definition

Represents an element that participates in composition.

In this Article

public interface ICompositionElement

Properties

DisplayName

Gets the display name of the composition element.

public string DisplayName { get; }
Value
String

The human-readable display name of the ICompositionElement.

Remarks

Implementers of this property should never return null or an empty string ("").

Origin

Gets the composition element from which the current composition element originated.

public System.ComponentModel.Composition.Primitives.ICompositionElement Origin { get; }
Value
ICompositionElement

The composition element from which the current ICompositionElement originated, or null if the ICompositionElement is the root composition element.
